# Autonomous Support Operations

See [AUTONOMOUS_SUPPORT_OPERATIONS.md](../../AUTONOMOUS_SUPPORT_OPERATIONS.md).

## Rules

1. Never hide uncertainty — escalate when confidence &lt;50% or risk is high/critical.
2. Autonomy level 0–3 is tenant-controlled; default level 1 (assisted).
3. Auto-reply only when: level ≥2, confidence ≥ threshold, low risk, category allows, BDE draft succeeds.
4. Triage uses Business DNA (templates, knowledge, escalation) — never bypass BDE.
5. Full audit via `support_audit_logs`; platform sees aggregates only.
6. Route: `/app/settings/support-operations` (spec `/admin/support-operations`).
7. i18n: `customerApp.supportOperations.*`, `platform.supportOperations.*` in en/no/sv/da.

## Tables

`aso_settings` · `support_categories` · `support_cases` · `support_audit_logs` · `support_knowledge_gaps` · `support_proactive_alerts`
